+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CMRwmpfCz6N7W6t4ac3UMu","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile the full review.\n\n---\n\n## Code Review: Fix all 6 monorepo breakages from botched merge/refactor\n\n### Strengths\n\n1. **All 6 breakages correctly identified and fixed.** Each fix is minimal and targeted, touching only the files that needed changing. The single commit (`7e27e21`) addresses all issues without introducing extraneous changes.\n\n2. **Circular dependency resolution is clean.** The `userExists` function and its `import { getUserById } from './user.js'` were surgically removed from `/workspace/packages/core/src/types.ts`, which is the correct approach -- `types.ts` should be a leaf module with no imports from business-logic modules. No callers of `userExists` existed elsewhere, so the removal is safe.\n\n3. **Merge conflict resolution chose the correct branch.** The conflict in `/workspace/packages/api/tests/users.test.ts` was resolved by keeping the `refactor/user-system` version (which includes `role: 'user'` in the request body) while retaining the original test description `'creates user with valid data'`. This is the correct choice because:\n   - The `createUserSchema` in `validation.ts` requires `role` as a mandatory field\n   - The test now sends data that matches the schema, so it actually passes validation\n\n4. **tsconfig project references are in correct dependency order.** `core` is now listed first in `/workspace/tsconfig.json`, before `api` and `worker`, which both depend on `core` via their own `references`. This ensures `tsc -b` builds the dependency graph correctly.\n\n5. **Zod version upgrade is appropriate.** Moving from the pinned `3.19.0` to `^3.22.0` in `/workspace/packages/core/package.json` correctly enables `z.pipe()` support used in `/workspace/packages/core/src/validation.ts` (lines 20-22, 28-30, 33-36). The resolved version `3